"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:1.5.3.6\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">1.5.3.6</span> 標題：編織或針織材料（woven or knitted material）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">經文出處</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： דַּלָּה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： dalah)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa38:12\">ISA 38:12</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： עֵרֶב</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： ‘erev)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:38\">EXO 12:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:48\">LEV 13:48</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:49\">LEV 13:49</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:51\">LEV 13:51</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:52\">LEV 13:52</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:53\">LEV 13:53</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:56\">LEV 13:56</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:57\">LEV 13:57</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:58\">LEV 13:58</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:59\">LEV 13:59</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:3\">NEH 13:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer25:20\">JER 25:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer50:37\">JER 50:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek30:5\">EZK 30:5</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： שְׁתִי</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： shthi)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:48\">LEV 13:48</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:49\">LEV 13:49</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:51\">LEV 13:51</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:52\">LEV 13:52</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:53\">LEV 13:53</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:56\">LEV 13:56</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:57\">LEV 13:57</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:58\">LEV 13:58</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:59\">LEV 13:59</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl10:17\">ECC 10:17</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述和用途</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0347_weaving.jpg\" alt=\"編織布\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">編織布 (Source unknown)</figcaption></figure>See <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">1.5.3 Cloth manufacture&lt;REALIA:1.5.3&gt;</a> 參<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">1.5.3 布料生產 (cloth manufacture)&lt;REALIA:1.5.3&gt;</a> 。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻譯</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>以下內容改寫自《〈利未記〉手冊》（<em>A Handbook on Leviticus</em> ，第200頁）對<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:48\">LEV 13:48</a> 的註解：<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"King James Version (1611)\">KJV</abbr> 和<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 等較早的譯本將希伯來文<em>shthi</em> 和<em>‘erev</em> 譯為“warp”（「經線」）和“woof”（「緯線」），這兩個詞在現代希伯來文中也是相同的含義。這種譯法表示布料上的線具有不同的方向。但是，這不太可能是經文的意思。很難明白為什麼一個方向上的線受到霉爛的影響，然而與其成直角的其他線卻不受影響。發霉部分需要撕去的要求也沒有道理（第56節），因為這樣做會破壞整件衣服。這些詞的含義可能是「編織或針織材料」（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New American Bible (1970)\">NAB</abbr> 、<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Traduction Oecuménique de la Bible (French, 1975)\">TOB</abbr> 、<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New International Version (1984)\">NIV</abbr> 直譯；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"American Translation (Goodspeed, 1935)\">AT</abbr> 的譯文類似），不過這種解釋並不確定。<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 將其簡化，英文直譯為「（衣服的）一塊」，但是翻譯者應該盡量避免這種簡化。</p>\n<p>在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa38:12\">ISA 38:12</a> ，希西家哀嘆他的壽命會縮短。他用了織布的比喻，說他的生命就像布料沿著織布機的經線（豎線）被剪斷。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
